The paper deals with lower bounds on the rank of matrices, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The paper uses techniques from algebraic geometry, combinatorics, and graph theory, which are commonly used in the subfields of computational complexity theory such as circuit complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and scientific computing (cs.SC). Therefore, these sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
